# Angular & TypeScript Standards

## TypeScript
- Use strict type checking; prefer type inference when obvious
- Avoid `any`; use `unknown` when type is uncertain

## Angular
- Standalone components (default in v20+; do NOT set `standalone: true`)
- Use signals for state; `computed()` for derived state
- Lazy load feature routes
- Use `host` object instead of `@HostBinding` / `@HostListener`
- Use `NgOptimizedImage` for static images (not inline base64)

## Components
- Small, single-responsibility; use `input()` and `output()` (not decorators)
- `changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush`
- Reactive forms over template-driven
- Use `class` and `style` bindings instead of `ngClass` / `ngStyle`
- External templates/styles: paths relative to component TS file

## State
- Signals for local state; use `update` or `set`, never `mutate`

## Templates
- Native control flow: `@if`, `@for`, `@switch` (not `*ngIf`, `*ngFor`, `*ngSwitch`)
- Async pipe for observables; no globals or arrow functions in templates

## Services
- Single responsibility; `providedIn: 'root'`; use `inject()` not constructor injection

## Accessibility
- Must pass AXE checks and WCAG AA (focus management, color contrast, ARIA)
